TWO bodies of men were discovered riddled with bullets
outside their home in Canelands KwaZulu Natal. According to Reaction Unit South Africa’s Prem Balram, they
received a call from a man requesting assistance for two men who had been shot
at an informal settlement on Station Road. In a statement, Balram said on arrival at the scene, both
men were found lying outside their home. “They had been shot multiple times and died at the scene.
Eleven spent 9mm cartridges were recovered in the vicinity of the bodies. One
cartridge was recovered inside a room where one of the murdered men resided,”
said Balram. Blood was also discovered on his bed and Residents of the
informal settlement gathered at the scene but claimed to have seen or heard
nothing.